.subsubsection The Notes Editor

.imagetext clinical/progressnotes/editor/progressnotes_editor_features.png

.bold Editor Buttons 
The progress notes is a mini-html editor with some very basic features.

 Note that the imageson your buttons may differ from these shown below:

.image clinical/progressnotes/editor/progressnotes_editor_btn_clear.png
 clears the contents of the editor with a popup warning.

.image clinical/progressnotes/editor/progressnotes_editor_btn_bold.png
 make text bold

.image clinical/progressnotes/editor/progressnotes_editor_btn_italic.png
 make text bold

.image clinical/progressnotes/editor/progressnotes_editor_btn_uline.png
 make text bold

.image clinical/progressnotes/editor/progressnotes_editor_align_left.png
 align text left
 

.image clinical/progressnotes/editor/progressnotes_editor_align_centre.png
 align text centre

.image clinical/progressnotes/editor/progressnotes_editor_align_right.png
 align text right

.image clinical/progressnotes/editor/progressnotes_editor_align_justify.png
 justify text (space evenly across the line)

.image clinical/progressnotes/editor/progressnotes_editor_align_font_size.png
 increase or decrease font size

.image clinical/progressnotes/editor/progressnotes_editor_align_font_color.png
 change the font color

.image clinical/progressnotes/editor/progressnotes_editor_align_add_file.png
 load data from external file or image

.end imagetext

.paragraph Editor Key Words

Certain words typed from within the editor invoke certain actions:
.item 
.draw - pops up a drawing editor
.item 
.mc   - pops up a medical certificate
.item 
.dx   - To code the consultation with a diagnosis, type .dx followed by whatever you wish to pop up up a list diagnostic terms.